               ResponseType responseType,

        Pass a document to the endpoint and retrieve the annotated results.
        Parameters:
        content - an input stream from which the document content can be read.
        mimeType - the MIME type identifying the document format, see the GATE documentation for a list of supported MIME types.
        responseType - requested response format
        annotationSelectors - annotation selector expressions specifying which annotation types to return.

        an open InputStream containing the API response, this stream must be closed by the caller once it has been read.

      • call

        public InputStream call(InputStream content,
               String mimeType,
               ResponseType responseType,
               String annotationSelectors,
               boolean includeText,
               String... queryParameters)
        Pass a document to the endpoint and retrieve the annotated results.
        Parameters:
        content - an input stream from which the document content can be read..
        mimeType - the MIME type identifying the document format, see the GATE documentation for a list of supported MIME types.
        responseType - requested response format
        annotationSelectors - annotation selector expressions specifying which annotation types to return.
        includeText - should the response include the document text or just the annotations? Returning just annotations is only supported by the GATE_XML and FINF response types.
        queryParameters - additional query parameters to be appended to the endpoint URL, specified as an alternating sequence of keys and values. The keys and values will be URL-encoded by this method, they should not be encoded in advance by the caller.
        Returns:
        an open InputStream containing the API response, this stream must be closed by the caller once it has been read.

        Pass a document to the endpoint and retrieve the annotated results.
        Parameters:
        content - a StreamWritable that can write the document content to an output stream.
        mimeType - the MIME type identifying the document format, see the GATE documentation for a list of supported MIME types.
        responseType - requested response format

        includeText - should the response include the document text or just the annotations? Returning just annotations is only supported by the GATE_XML and FINF response types.
        queryParameters - additional query parameters to be appended to the endpoint URL, specified as an alternating sequence of keys and values. The keys and values will be URL-encoded by this method, they should not be encoded in advance by the caller.
